Again, whereas our Lord <normalised orig="commandeth" auto="true">commands</normalised>, Mar. 10. <quote type="biblical" ana="Mk 10.14">Suffer <normalised orig="litle" auto="true">little</normalised><lb/>
children to come unto me &amp; forbid them not.</quote> How properly can<lb/>
an Infant come unto Christ but by <normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised>? repent they cannot;<lb/>
<normalised orig="beleeve" auto="true">believe</normalised> <choice ana="print-error">
                     <sic>the</sic>
                     <corr>they</corr>
                  </choice> cannot, as the Anabaptists <normalised orig="affirme" auto="true">affirm</normalised>; But by<lb/>
<normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised> they may come, where the Minister in Christs stead <normalised orig="receiveth" auto="true">receives</normalised><lb/>
