Learned Mr. Calvin <normalised orig="affirmeth" auto="true">affirms</normalised> the <normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised> of children to be a<lb/>
holy institution <normalised orig="alwayes" auto="true">always</normalised> observed in Christs Church.<lb/>
All the reformed Churches use it, and it <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> <normalised orig="beene" auto="true">been</normalised> the practise<lb/>
of the <normalised orig="universall" auto="true">universal</normalised> Church.<lb/>
The Greek Church (who <normalised orig="yearely" auto="true">yearly</normalised> excommunicate the Pope)<lb/>
to whom St. Paul preached <normalised orig="baptize" auto="true">baptise</normalised> their Infants, as Gregory<lb/>
